5 April 2025 **Land Transport Act 1998** Part 4A s 30D


**30E Additional criteria for large passenger service**

```
Without in any way limiting the matters that the Director may have regard to
under section 30C(2), when the Director is assessing whether or not a person is
a fit and proper person in relation to any large passenger service, the Director
must consider, in particular,—
(a) any history of serious behavioural problems that indicate a propensity
for violence:
(b) any offending in respect of offences of violence or sexual offences:
(c) any offending in respect of major transport-related offences, particularly
offences relating to safety or to road user charges.
Compare: 1989 No 74 s 24(2)(b)
Section 30E: inserted, on 1 October 2007, by section 18 of the Land Transport Amendment Act 2005
