**30F Additional criteria for goods service**

```
Without in any way limiting the matters that the Director may have regard to
under section 30C(2), when the Director is assessing whether or not a person
is a fit and proper person in relation to any goods service, the Director must
consider, in particular,—
(a) any criminal activity conducted in the course of any transport service or
transport-related business or employment:
(b) any offending in respect of major transport-related offences, particularly
offences relating to safety or to road user charges.
Compare: 1989 No 74 s 24(2)(c)
