**30H Director’s duties concerning prejudicial information**

```
If the Director proposes to take into account any information that is or may
be prejudicial to the person, the Director must, subject to section 30I(1) and
to subpart 5, disclose that information to the person and, in accordance with
subpart 5, give the person a reasonable opportunity to refute or comment on it.
Compare: 1989 No 74 s 24(5)
