**30T Procedure Director must follow before revoking transport service licence**

```
If the proposed revocation of a licence under section 30S is on the ground that
a person other than the licence holder is not a fit and proper person,—
(a) the notice required to be given to the licence holder by section 30W
must specify the steps that the Director will require to be taken if the
licence is not to be revoked, which steps may include a requirement
that the person concerned cease all involvement in the service within a
specified period; and
(b) the licence must not be revoked where the licence holder complies with
any such requirements of the Director.
Compare: 1989 No 74 s 11(2), (3)
Section 30T: inserted, on 1 October 2007, by section 18 of the Land Transport Amendment Act 2005
(2005 No 77).
