**30U Suspension of transport service licence or imposition of conditions**

(1) The Director may suspend or impose conditions on a licence if—

```
(a) the holder of a transport service licence, or any person who has control
of the service, does not hold a certificate required by the regulations or
the rules; or
(b) the holder of a transport service licence, or any person who has control
of the service, does not comply with the applicable requirements in this
Part, Part 4B, the regulations, or the rules; or
(c) the holder of a small passenger service licence does not have—
(i) a person with control of the service in New Zealand who lives in
New Zealand; or
(ii) a representative who lives in New Zealand.
```
(2) A suspension ceases immediately when the Director is satisfied that subsection
(1)(a), (b), or (c) no longer applies.

5 April 2025 **Land Transport Act 1998** Part 4A s 30U


(2A) Any conditions imposed are immediately removed when the Director is satis‐
fied that subsection (1)(a), (b), or (c) no longer applies.

(3) Subpart 5 applies to a decision to suspend a transport service licence.

(4) Subpart 5 applies to a decision to impose conditions on a transport service
licence as if the licence had been suspended and with any necessary modifica‐
tions.
Compare: 1989 No 74 s 18(4), (5)
