(1) A person commits an offence if the person holds or applies for a driver licence
while disqualified from doing so or while his or her driver licence is suspen‐
ded.

(1A) Subsection (1) does not apply in relation to—

```
(a) an application for an alcohol interlock licence made in accordance with
an alcohol interlock sentence; or
(b) an application for a zero alcohol licence made in accordance with section
65B.
```
