**36B Contravention of section 22B or section 22C**

(1) A person commits an offence if the person—

```
(a) uses a traction engine without an appropriate qualification provided for
in the regulations or the rules, for the purpose of qualifying the person to
safely use the traction engine in a public place; or
(b) uses a traction engine in a public place in a manner that, having regard
to all the circumstances, is or might be dangerous to the public or to a
person; or
(c) uses a traction engine in a public place without displaying current evi‐
dence of vehicle inspection or any other certificate or both (as may be
required by the regulations or the rules); or
(d) fails to comply with the regulations or the rules concerning evidence of
vehicle inspection or any other certificate required by the regulations or
the rules, or concerning the use of a traction engine that is required to
have such evidence or certificate or both.
```
(2) The maximum penalty on conviction for an offence against subsection (1) is a
fine not exceeding $5,000.

(3) For the purposes of this section, **public place** has the meaning set out in
section 22B(3).
Section 36B: inserted, on 16 January 2006, by section 24 of the Land Transport Amendment Act
2005 (2005 No 77).

