**55 Tampering with vehicle surveillance equipment or point-to-point average
speed system**

(1) A person commits an offence if the person—

```
(a) tampers with approved vehicle surveillance equipment or a point-to-
point average speed system; or
(b) interferes with—
(i) approved vehicle surveillance equipment or a point-to-point aver‐
age speed system; or
(ii) the operation of approved vehicle surveillance equipment or a
point-to-point average speed system.
```
(2) The maximum penalty on conviction for an offence against subsection (1) is a
fine not exceeding $5,000.
Compare: 1962 No 135 s 42(2)

5 April 2025 **Land Transport Act 1998** Part 5 s 55


