**87E Procedure for suspending persons under section 87D**

(1) If the Director suspends a person under section 87D, the notice must—

```
(a) inform the person of the grounds of the suspension; and
(b) advise the person that—
(i) the suspension has effect from the day on which the notice was
received by the person, or any later date that is specified in the
notice; and
(ii) the person may make submissions on the matter to the Director
and that the person has a right of appeal under section 106.
```
(2) The Director must, as soon as practicable, consider any submissions on the
matter made by the person and notify the person of the result of the consider‐
ation.

5 April 2025 **Land Transport Act 1998** Part 7 s 87E


```
