**100 Director to remove certain disqualifications**

(1) If an order has been made under section 65 in respect of a person ( **the appli‐
cant** ), the Director must make an order removing the disqualification of the
applicant from holding or obtaining a driver licence, if satisfied that—
(a) the applicant is a fit person to hold a driver licence, having regard to—
(i) a report which is from a health practitioner attached to an assess‐
ment centre and which is made available to the Director by the
applicant or the assessment centre; and
(ii) any other evidence submitted by the applicant or otherwise avail‐
able to the Director relating to the medical condition of the appli‐
cant.
(b) _[Repealed]_

(2) If the Director makes an order under subsection (1), every order made under
section 65 that applies to the applicant concerned must be treated as having
expired.

(3) No order may be made under subsection (1) if the applicant concerned is
subject to an order made under section 65 that has been in force less than 1
year and 1 day.

(4) If the Director decides not to remove the disqualification under subsection (1),
the Director must refer the applicant to the right of appeal under section 108.
Compare: 1962 No 135 s 30C
