(b) evidence of that person’s identity.

(4) A dangerous goods enforcement officer may, if authorised (either generally or
specifically) in writing for the purpose by the Director or the Commissioner,
take a person or animal onto the premises to assist the officer with an inspec‐
tion, and a person assisting the officer has the powers conferred on a dangerous
goods enforcement officer by this section.

(5) Nothing in this section limits or affects the privilege against self incrimination.
