## 149 Admissibility of certain statements by drivers of certain vehicles

(1) A statement made to an enforcement officer, or to a person authorised for that
purpose by the Agency or the Director, to the effect described in subsection
(2) may be given in evidence by that officer or person and is admissible in
evidence in proceedings for an offence against this Act as evidence of the
matters referred to in the statement.

(2) A statement referred to in subsection (1) must be to the effect that the state‐
ment—
(a) was made by the driver of—
(i) a vehicle that is or ought to be used in a transport service (other
than a rental service); or
(ii) a heavy motor vehicle; and
(b) was made to an enforcement officer or to a person authorised for that
purpose by the Agency or the Director; and
(c) relates to the identity of the employer of that driver or a matter that is or
ought to be specified in a logbook.
Compare: 1962 No 135 s 196A

Part 10 s 149 **Land Transport Act 1998**
5 April 2025


