## 152A Governor-General may make ordinary rules

(1) Despite anything in this Part, the Governor-General may, by Order in Council,
on the recommendation of the Minister, make, amend, or revoke an ordinary
rule for any of the purposes for which the Minister may make, amend, or
revoke an ordinary rule under this Part.

(2) The Minister must have regard to the criteria specified in section 164(2) before
making a recommendation under subsection (1).

(3) Section 161(1)(a) and (2) do not apply to an ordinary rule made by Order in
Council under subsection (1).

