**161 Procedure concerning ordinary rules**

(1) Every ordinary rule must—

```
(a) be signed by the Minister; and
(b) contain a statement specifying the objective of the rule and the extent of
any consultation under subsection (2); and
(c) set out fully the requirements of the rule, except where certain informa‐
tion is incorporated in the rule by reference under section 165.
```
(2) Before making an ordinary rule, the Minister must—

```
(a) publish a notice of his or her intention to make the rule; and
```
Part 11 s 161 **Land Transport Act 1998**
5 April 2025


```
(b) give interested persons a reasonable time, which must be specified in
the notice published under paragraph (a), to make submissions on the
proposal; and
(c) consult with such persons, representative groups within the land trans‐
port system or elsewhere, government departments, and Crown entities
as the Minister in each case considers appropriate.
```
