**169 Objectives of Minister**

```
The objectives of the Minister under this Act are—
(a) to undertake the Minister’s functions in a way that contributes to an
integrated, safe, responsive, and sustainable transport system; and
(b) to ensure that New Zealand’s obligations under international agreements
relating to land transport are implemented.
Section 169: substituted, on 1 December 2004, by section 6 of the Land Transport Amendment Act
2004 (2004 No 96).
