## 212 Agency to pay sum to assessment centres

```
The Agency must pay each assessment centre, from money appropriated for the
purpose by Parliament, such sum as may be prescribed for the first attendance
of a person ordered under this Act to attend an assessment centre, if that person
has not previously attended an assessment centre following the making of the
order.
Compare: 1962 No 135 s 30B(3)
