is repealed by this Act, which application is pending immediately before the
repeal of that provision, may be determined under the corresponding provision
of this Act.
```
## 229 Savings relating to rules and land transport strategies

(1) Any action taken by or on behalf of the Minister before the commencement of
this section under section 10(1) of the Land Transport Act 1993, which action
was taken in relation to any proposed rule under that Act, is deemed to have
been taken by the Minister under, and for the purposes of, section 161(2) of this
Act before the making of the rule.

(2) Any action taken by or on behalf of the Minister before the commencement of
this section under section 29B of the Land Transport Act 1993, which action
was taken in relation to any proposed national land transport strategy under that
Act, is deemed to have been taken by the Minister under, and for the purposes
of, section 171 of this Act before the making of the strategy.

(3) Any national land transport strategy and regional land transport strategy in
force under Part 3A of the Land Transport Act 1993 immediately before the
commencement of Part 13 of this Act has effect as if made under that Part.

